      "type": "prov:Entity",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior computational hemolysis studies for centrifugal pumps",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis drawing on more than a dozen peer-reviewed computational hemolysis studies published between 2008 and 2022, covering multiple turbulence model comparisons, blood damage model formulations (power-law and strain-based), and mesh sensitivity analyses for rotary blood pumps. This synthesis informed the turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), the Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis power-law exponents adopted in the present model, and the acceptance thresholds for discretization error. The breadth and depth of the underlying literature base make this node a de-facto foundational reference within the credibility chain."
