    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 for a Class II device with medium model influence. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient predictive fidelity (mean NIH error 8.3%, GCI 2.1%) to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions under the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The credibility body of evidence is accepted as adequate to support the regulatory submission decision.",
